]] (A.B. 1961), Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for Political and Military Affairs\n\n====Military====\n*[[William Atwater (curator)|William Atwater]] (M.A., Ph.D. 1982), retired captain in the US Marines; author, historian, and director of the US Army Ordnance Museum\n*[[Walter E. Boomer]] (B.S. 1960), retired general, former assistant commandant, US Marine Corps, [[Desert Storm]] Commander; business executive\n*[[Frank Bowman]] (B.S. 1966), retired admiral, former Chief of Naval Personnel, former director of Naval Nuclear Propulsion, US Navy; Honorary [[Order of the British Empire|Knight Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire]] (KBE)\n*[[Winston Choo]] (MA, History), retired [[lieutenant-general]], former Chief of Defence Force (1974-1992) in the [[Singapore Armed Forces]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acsclass57.com/bio/winston_choo.htm|title=Winston Choo Wee Leong|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://infopediatalk.nl.sg/biographies/SIP_1539_2009-06-30/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-10-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090708050804/http://infopediatalk.nl.sg/biographies/SIP_1539_2009-06-30/ |archivedate=July 8, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n*[[Edward H. Deets]] (1979), rear admiral in the [[United States Navy]]\n*[[Martin E. Dempsey]] (M.A. 1984), [[Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff]]\n*[[Charles S. Hamilton]] (B.S. 1974), rear admiral in the [[United States Navy]]\n*[[John L. Helgerson]] (M.S., Ph.D.), former [[CIA Inspector General]]\n*[[James W. Holsinger]] (M.D. 1964), retired [[Major general (United States)|major general]] in the [[United States Army Reserve]], [[physician]], nominated to become the 18th [[Surgeon General of the United States]]\n*[[Gilmary M. Hostage III]] (B.S.E. 1977), [[United States Air Force]] four-star general, currently serving as the commander of [[Air Combat Command]]\n*[[Vergel L. Lattimore]], brigadier general in the [[Air National Guard]]\n*[[Ng Jui Ping]] (MA