m Duke University School of Law.\n*In the pilot episode of ''[[Privileged (TV series)|Privileged]]'', billionaire Laurel Limoges hires recent Yale graduate Megan Smith to tutor her two granddaughters with the goal of getting them into Duke.\n* Stingo, the narrator of William Styron's novel ''[[Sophie's Choice (novel)|Sophie's Choice]]'', attended Duke as an undergraduate (as did Styron).\n*[[List of House characters#Stacy Warner|Stacy Warner]] lawyer and ex-girlfriend of main character [[Gregory House|Dr. House]] on the TV series ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'', played by [[Sela Ward]], hired as the hospital's lawyer during [[House (Season 2)|season 2]]\n* Charlotte York's brother Wesley on ''[[Sex and the City]]''\n* Quentin, the protagonist of the novel ''[[Paper Towns]]'' and its [[Paper Towns (film)|film adaptation]], is an incoming freshman at Duke.\n* Natalie, the protagonist of the movie ''[[Keith (film)|Keith]]'', is a high school tennis star who dreams of going to Duke.\n* [[Nathan Scott]], one of the protagonists of the television series ''One Tree Hill'', though his offer was rescinded when he was caught [[point shaving]]\n* [[Haley James Scott]], one of the protagonists of the television series ''One Tree Hill'', though she decided not to attend after she became pregnant with her son and her husband's offer was rescinded\n\n==Faculty==\n\n===Current===\n[[File:Walter E. Dellinger III.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Walter E. Dellinger III]]]]\n[[File:Henry Petroski Photo.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Henry Petroski]]]]\n[[File:Erwin chemerinsky 09-2007.JPG|thumb|right|150px|[[Erwin Chemerinsky]]]]\n\n*[[Bill Adair (journalist)|Bill Adair]],  founder of the [[Pulitzer Prize]]-winning website [[PolitiFact]]\n*[[David Aers]], [[James B. Duke Professor]] of English, expert on medieval and Renaissance literature and theology\n*[[Pankaj K. Agarwal]], computer scientist, known for his research on [[computational geometry]]\n*[[Susan Alberts]], primatologist, co-director of [